description.narrative: Supporting Women's Transformative Leadership in Changing Times AND Democratic Transition 2012-2015 (AMAL programme). Oxfam in Maghreb Office contribution to the AMAL programme covers Tunisia and includes: 1. Overall management and coordination of the programme inTunisia: Set and chair the steering committee, monitor the progress of AMAL, harmonize the partners interventions within the set logframe, ensure timely implementation of the workplan 2. Provide the technical support to partners: Identify thecapacity gaps within the partner organizations and develop and implement with them a capacity building plan, support the partners in the implementation of their workplans, etc 3. MEAL: Conduct the baseline, ensure the accurate reporting as per donor's agreement 4. Ensure appropriate financial management as per the donor's agreement and guidelines 5. Liaise with the regional management team of the programme for theregional component of AMAL

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
